items.title: Vodafone Idea moves SC against DoT's calculation behind fresh AGR dues
items.description: Vodafone Idea has filed a petition before the Supreme Court challenging the AGR calculation, Moneycontrol has learnt.

items.title: GSK working on affordable vaccines for neglected diseases, partnership with India key: Jamila Louahed
items.description: Jamila Louahed - VP, Head Global R&D for Therapeutic Vaccines and Belgium R&D Site Head for GSK outlined how the pharma major's innovations are being deployed to tackle diseases like malaria, typhoid, tuberculosis, and Shigella.

items.title: Ice cream maker Vadilal appoints former HUL professional as first CEO outside promoter family
items.description: A former HUL executive and a consumer business professional, Himanshu Kanwar held multiple leadership roles across foods, beverages, and personal care divisions, and was the Business Head for Ice Creams.

items.title: Bikaji Foods' managing director summoned in-person by ED in connection with a PMLA probe
items.description: Clarifying that there is no financial impact on the business at this stage, Bikaji Foods said the company is not under any default in the matter.

items.title: GST reforms positive for defence manufacturers, but benefits for listed players likely limited
items.description: Some companies, including Hindustan Aeronautics (HAL) in helicopters and Solar Industries in drones, may see incremental advantages, but analysts stress that these are unlikely to translate into significant margin expansion.

items.title: OPINION | Leading from the Front: Transforming solitude into leadership
items.description: Leadership is often lonely, requiring inner strength and authenticity. True leadership emerges from alignment with values, embracing solitude, and transforming challenges into growth, not just for oneself, but for the greater mission

items.title: IRCTC – Can it leverage the consumption push to gain speed?

items.title: OPINION | Why MSMEs should embrace online dispute resolution to address payment delays
items.description: India’s MSMEs face cash flow challenges due to delayed payments and tariffs. The government’s Online Dispute Resolution portal offers a timely solution to resolve payment disputes efficiently

items.title: Karnataka: Honda’s Rs 600 crore electric two-wheeler manufacturing unit to start operations soon
items.description: A state government-led delegation headed by Industries Minister MB Patil is in Japan and held talks with Tokyo Electron, Mitsubishi Electric, Honda, Yokogawa Electric, and Restar to attract investments and expand trade.
